<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-03-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-03-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="569" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d569">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Day</persName> to Señor
                                    <persName type="to">Polo de Bernabé</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-03-28"><hi rend="italic">March 28,
                                1898</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Minister</hi>: I have to acknowledge
                            receipt of your note of 26th instant, informing me that you had
                            telegraphed to H. E. the Governor-General of Cuba, advising him of the
                            arrival at Matanzas of the Norwegian steamer <hi rend="italic">Ulstein</hi>, and requesting that all possible facilities and
                            franchises be extended to that vessel, provided the cargo only contains
                            goods for the relief of the reconcentrados.</p>
                        <p>Accept my thanks for your courtesy and prompt cooperation in this matter,
                            and believe me,</p>
                        <p>Very truly, yours,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">William R. Day.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>